<h2 id="section-top">Gastrointestinal and Liver services</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=969">Kettering General Hospital NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address"><br/>01536 493646</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent7939473cfb9c4467993171f0f8d6e5d7">
</div>
<p>The department of gastroenterology provides an integrated service for patients with digestive diseases. We offer a number of service including our viral hepatitis service, inflammatory bowel cancer screening, and endoscopy services.</p>
<p><strong>Viral Hepatitis Service</strong></p>
<p>This service is led by our consultant hepatologist and supported by the nurse specialists with ongoing evaluation, monitoring and delivery of hepatitis C treatments. This includes an inreach service to Wellingborough HMP.</p>
<p> <strong>IBD services</strong></p>
<p>Our clinical nurse specialists provide follow up clinics for selected <a href="../../../../conditions/inflammatory-bowel-disease/pages/introduction.aspx">IBD</a> patients. They assist in the management of complex ambulatory GI patients and deliver all biological treatments for IBD patients. There is a designated helpline service for IBD patients allowing rapid access for assessment if clinically needed.</p>
<p> <strong>Bowel Cancer Screening Centre</strong></p>
<p>Kettering is the screening centre for the countywide Bowel Cancer Screening Program. We provide comprehensive bowel cancer screening to people in Leicester, Rutland and Northamptonshire, covering a population of 1.7 million.</p>
<p>Click <a href="../../../../conditions/cancer-of-the-colon-rectum-or-bowel/pages/introduction.aspx" target="_blank">here</a> to find out more about bowel cancer screening.</p>
<p><strong>Endoscopy service</strong></p>
<p>We have a high quality JAG accredited endoscopy Unit. It has three procedure rooms with a full range of endoscopic equipment. As well as our highly trained physicians we have three extensively trained nurse endoscopists all providing a diverse range of endoscopies, from gastroscopies to colonoscopy. Capsule endoscopy service is also provided and assists in diagnosing gastrointestinal conditions such as obscure gastrointestinal bleeding, malabsorption, chronic abdominal pain, and chronic diarrhoea, and can be particularly useful when looking at possible conditions in the small intestine.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel name-serviceteamsummary">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear"><h3><a href="/Services/clinics/Services/Service/Team/DefaultView.aspx?id=1867">Staff</a></h3>
<div id="imageContentde483fa827cf4a9f9b94d6a94c25228e">
</div>
<p>We have a large team of dedicated professionals working to make sure the community are provided with excellent high quality services. We perform 7500 procedures annually. There are a number of staff on hand in the two medical wards and in the endoscopy department.</p><p><a href="/Services/clinics/Services/Service/Team/DefaultView.aspx?id=1867">Learn more about our staff</a></p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
